descriptor.name: Banana Elaichi
descriptor.short_desc: Short Description - Banana Elichi or Yelakki are small sized bananas. They are just like regular bananas in taste but are more sweeter. descriptor.name: Baby Shimla Apple(Approx.12-14 Nos)
descriptor.short_desc: Short Description - Shimla apples come in a variety of sizes and shapes, ranging from little to large and round to oblate to conical in shape. Waxy, glossy, or smooth skin in red, green, yellow, or orange tones is possible. The skin can be plain or bi-colored with striping and blush. The flesh might be firm, pale yellow to cream-colored, juicy, crunchy, or crisp, depending on the variety. Shimla apples come in a variety of flavors, from sweet to sour, and can have a strong or subtle smell.

descriptor.name: Kanda Lasun Masala
descriptor.short_desc: Short Description - Kisankonnect Kanda Lasun Masla -Foods from the western ghats in general cuisine of Maharashtra is the masala the people of the ghats use in their cooking. It is, for want of a better name, simply described as Ghati Masala.  Earlier it was made it on a very large quantity and save it for the whole year as the process to make this masala is very tedious and time consuming. The whole process consists right from roasting 3 types of chillies, 18 different types of spices which are used. Followed by frying onion, Garlic and dry coconut in it. A typical Maharashtrian family uses only this particular blend in their daily food preparations, and that’s how we have got to know the secret behind the Bharala Vanga (Bharwa Baingan) or any Maharashtrian “Tarri Wala Curry"

descriptor.name: Wheat Flour (Sharbati)
descriptor.short_desc: Short Description - Wheat atta ( Sharbati ) is a fresh atta type. It is freshly grounded before 48hrs. It originates from sehore region of Madhya Pradesh.
